Mexico Stocks: America Movil, Cemex Shares Retreat; Telmex Gains

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-08-02T21:12:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/mexico-stocks-america-movil-cemex-shares-retreat-telmex-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index declined 2.6 percent to 34,814.94.  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , slipped 1.7 percent to
14.58 pesos, adding to declines after yesterday announcing an
offer to buy the 40.4 percent of Telefonos de Mexico SAB it
doesn’t already own.  Telefonos de Mexico (TELMEXL MM), Mexico’s largest fixed-
line telephone company, jumped 2.6 percent to 10.49 pesos,
converging on the 10.50 pesos a share America Movil said it
would pay.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, tumbled 6.1 percent to 7.52 pesos. U.S. consumer
spending unexpectedly dropped in June for the first time in
almost two years, declining 0.2 percent after a 0.1 percent gain
the prior month, Commerce Department figures showed today in
 Washington .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
